<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-14T20:26:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-14T20:26:00-05:00" n="83" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1351: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">Repeated for
                                    information to Baghdad as 321.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-14T20:26:00-05:00">December 14, 1951—8:26 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 471. Re <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 659 Dec 13 <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> suggests light possibility Iraq
                                voting for Byelorussia, <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                                might if it thinks useful approach <pb facs="0152" n="130" xml:id="pg_130"/> Jamali<note n="2" xml:id="d83fn2">Mohamed
                                    Padhil Al-Jamali, Chairman of the Delegation of Iraq to the
                                    General Assembly.</note> along fol lines: US keenly aware deep
                                interest Iraq in this issue and strongly hopes Jamali in position
                                urge his Govt’s unqualified support for Grk candidacy. Del shld play
                                on theme that US recognizes importance Iraqi Govt attaches Jamali’s
                                    recommendations;<note n="3" xml:id="d83fn3">Dr. Jamali was also
                                    President of the Iraqi Chamber of Deputies.</note> US therefore
                                approaching him Paris in hope he will recommend to his Govt that it
                                support Greece. Del cld also refer instances his valuable support in
                                past which we greatly appreciate.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>